    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-Pectobacterium Polypeptide-1 Arginyl sr-Spider Oligopeptide-1 Dipeptide-19 Hexapeptide-40 is a single chain recombinant fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sr-Pectobacterium Polypeptide-1, sr-Spider Oligopeptide-1, Dipeptide-19,  and Hexapeptide-40 with the initiation code for Arginine (q.v.). The fusion peptide contains 79 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
